    "body": "`Thread::start` is a low level interface to raw threads. It specifically doesn't do the initialization required to start up the runtime. The `spawn` function should be used instead:\n\n``` rust\nspawn(proc() {\n    while !*done.lock()) {}\n})\n```\n",
