    "body": "Aren't futures for returning a value? I mean technically it's returning `()`, but still...\nDo you know why `spawn` doesn't just return a reference to the spawned thread? Also is this still a bug, or what?\n\nMy adjustment to use `try_future`:\n\n``` rust\n//standard library imports\nuse std::rt::thread::Thread;\nuse std::sync::{ Arc, Mutex};\n\nfn main(){\n    //make mutex\n    let done = Arc::new( Mutex::new( false));\n\n    //spawn producer\n    println!(\"starting producer\");\n    let mut prod_done = done.clone();\n    let producer = std::task::try_future(\n        proc(){ *( prod_done.lock()) = true;});\n\n    //spawn consumer\n    println!(\"starting consumer\");\n    let consumer = std::task::try_future(\n        proc(){\n            while ! *( done.lock()) {}});\n\n    //finish up\n    println!(\"joining threads\");\n    producer.unwrap();\n    consumer.unwrap();\n    println!(\"threads joined\");\n}\n```\n",
    "author_association": "NONE",
